        <h2> By: Asher Williams </h2>
        <p>I enjoy a variety of hobbies in my free time. My favorite is basketball</p>
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1546519638-68e109498ffc?fm=jpg&q=60&w=3000&ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxzZWFyY2h8Nnx8YmFza2V0YmFsbCUyMGNvdXJ0fGVufDB8fDB8fHww" alt="Basketball" width="500" height="300" style="border: 2px solid black;">
        <h3>About Me</h3>
        <p><li>Basketball is a sport that I have played my whole life. I started playing when I was about 5 years old. I played on a team in my hometown of Bonners Ferry, Idaho. 
        <p><li> I played all the way through high school and now I play for <a href="https://www.mtech.edu/">Montana Tech</a>. I love the competitiveness of the game and the teamwork that is involved. It is a great way to stay in shape and have fun at the same time.</li></p>
        <img src="orediggers.jpeg" alt="Montana Tech Orediggers" width="300" height="300" style="border: 2px solid black;">

        <p><li>In high school, I was fortunate enough to break the all-time scoring record for my school. It was a great accomplishment for me and something that I am very proud of.</p>

        <p><li>Playing basketball has taught me a lot about discipline, hard work, and perseverance. I won two state championships and was named MVP of the tournament both times.</p>
