        <h1>My Outdoor Adventures</h1>
        <p>I love spending time outdoors, especially when it comes to fishing. There's something peaceful about being on the water and waiting for a bite.</p>
        <img src="fihsing.jpeg" alt="Fishing" width="600" height="400" style="border: 2px solid black;">
        <h2>Favorite Fishing Spots</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Moyie River, Idaho</li>
            <li>Bull Lake, Montana</li>
            <li>Kootenai River, Idaho</li>
        </ul>
        <h2>Fishing Tips</h2>
        <p>Here are a few tips I've learned over the years:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Be patient - sometimes it takes a while to get a bite.</li>
            <li>Use the right bait for the type of fish you're trying to catch. I enjoy fly fishing on the surface personally.</li>
            <li>Pay attention to the weather - fish are more active during certain conditions.</li>
